The House Committee on Judiciary, Non- Civil offers the following substitute to HB 464:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 3 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to justification and excuse relative to defenses to criminal prosecutions, so as to
3 provide for immunity for a prospective offender while seeking assistance from law
4 enforcement as a victim of a certain offenses; to provide for limitations regarding
5 prosecution; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 2 of Chapter 3 of Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
9 justification and excuse relative to defenses to criminal prosecutions, is amended by adding
10 a new Code section, to read as follows:
11 "16-3-22.2.
12 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'predominant aggressor' means the individual
13 who poses the most serious ongoing threat, and who may not be the initial aggressor in a
14 specific incident.
15 (b) Any victim of a violation of:
